T1  - Information Sharing As An Interorganizational Activity
AU  - Schermerhorn, John R.
Y1  - 1977/03/01
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255469
DO  - 10.5465/255469
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 148
EP  - 153
VL  - 20
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses a study which analyzed information sharing as an interorganizational activity. The research revealed a positive relationship between the information sharing activity and perceived level of organizational task accomplishment. Information sharing increased as the perception of organizational task performance levels increased. Information sharing was also positively associated to organizational size and type. It was negatively associated with employee tenure. Information sharing was associated with administrators of shorter tenure in larger, nonprofit organizations.
AB  - The article discusses a study which analyzed information sharing as an interorganizational activity. The research revealed a positive relationship between the information sharing activity and perceived level of organizational task accomplishment. Information sharing increased as the perception of organizational task performance levels increased. Information sharing was also positively associated to organizational size and type. It was negatively associated with employee tenure. Information sharing was associated with administrators of shorter tenure in larger, nonprofit organizations.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255469
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255469
